      <hedline>
        <hl1>The White Sox</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Connor Hauge letter notes April 30 What's Doing In article on Chicago ignored Chicago White SoxU</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: In your article ''What's Doing in Chicago'' (April 30), you mentioned the Chicago Cubs but ignored the Chicago White Sox.</p>
        <p>In his book ''Veeck as in Wreck,'' Bill Veeck, the team's former owner, described a scenario in which he invades a South Side home at 3 a.m. on a weeknight and shakes the homeowner awake. The question, ''Who are you?'' elicits the response, ''I'm a White Sox fan.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: In your article ''What's Doing in Chicago'' (April 30), you mentioned the Chicago Cubs but ignored the Chicago White Sox.</p>
        <p>In his book ''Veeck as in Wreck,'' Bill Veeck, the team's former owner, described a scenario in which he invades a South Side home at 3 a.m. on a weeknight and shakes the homeowner awake. The question, ''Who are you?'' elicits the response, ''I'm a White Sox fan.''</p>
        <p>The true baseball fans are at Comiskey Park, the home of the White Sox.</p>
        <p>CONNOR HAUGH  Poughkeepsie, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
